description.narrative:
This project falls under Oxfam Novib#s Strategic Partnership with the Dutch government and more specifically the Theory of Change for Finance for Development, aiming to achieve impact for more citizens to enjoy their basic rights and financial inclusion and experience equal opportunity in more democratic societies.
Oxfam Novib aims to achieve that more women, youth and other citizens benefitfrom higher quality and quantity of finance for development, an enhanced fiscal system and a sustainable and inclusive financial and corporate sector, tackling extreme inequality. To achieve the long-term outcome of the project, we use the following strategies: capacity building of civil society organizations, strengthening national and international coalitions, increase public pressure on governments and multinational corporations, increased media coverage, and increased political will.
Apart from working with Somo, to achieve the long-term outcome on a global scale, Oxfam works together with numerous partners, including Eurodad, Global Alliance forTax Justice (GATJ), and Tax Justice Network Nederland (TJN-NL). Oxfam Novib provides influencing support to Oxfam country offices and partners in Morocco, Egypt, Palestine, Niger, Nigeria, Uganda, Pakistan, Cambodia and Vietnam:
- From local to global:In the SP we are aiming to increasingly connect local influencing strategies to global campaign activities (e.g. in the Even it Up!Campaign) and to ensure that global advocacy is much better connected to and grounded in country level work. This happens by strengthening Southern influencing structures and working through regional campaign structures and regional partners, that connect to influencers and campaigners at country level.
- Globalsupport to the implementation of the SP in country offices (COs): The support to COs will be provided by The Hague office, in collaboration with global partners and allies. This will be tailor-made per country and can take various forms and shapes, including duty trips of global staff to provide technical support, face-to face meetings, consultancies, training workshops on tax justice, budget monitoring or tax avoidance (SOMO) and the financial sector (PROFUNDO/SOMO), exchange of best practices, digital campaigning support, fundraising support, public finance management tendering, case study research, power analysis and policy advocacy meetings or research support, based on clear ToRs.
- An annual global strategy meeting will be held with relevant COs and partners to exchange best practices, link, learn and jointly establish clear regional and international policy targets linking up to the Oxfam Even it Up! campaign (including linking to relevant global policy and campaigning teams).
- Finally, through policy influencing at decision-makers are targeted to influence decisions on taxation policies in the EU and the Netherlands, whilst raising awareness on tax justice among Dutch citizens through on-going communication/engagementwith the Dutch audience.

participating-org.narrative: Oxfam Novib was founded in 1956 as the Netherlands Organisation for International Assistance (Novib), and joined forces with Oxfam in 1994. Oxfam Novib is member of the Oxfam International confederation. Working together in the confederation, the Oxfam affiliates can speak with one clear and compelling voice on issues of global concern: climate change, health and education for all, agriculture, trade, and conflicts and emergencies. Oxfam Novib's main office is based in The Netherlands, it supports the work of a network of local offices, the implementation of global projects, fundraising, campaigning and advocacy. Oxfam Novib’s the Hague office contributes towards this project’s implementation.
